commitResults.messageTitle: Rename main class and add greeting
Add support for echo in Grump.java
Add support for list in Grump.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Add an ArrayList to store tasks and printTasks method to loop through
the ArrayList and print all the tasks with numbering from 1.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Task.java and support for mark and unmark in Grump.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Add Task.java to store the description and isDone fields.
Change ArrayList to store Task instead.
Add mark and unmark feature in Grump.java.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Todo.java, Event.java, Deadline.java and support for different tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Add Todo.java, Event.java and Deadline.java in which all inherit from
Task.java.
Add support for the identification of different type of tasks and
creating the correct object type before adding it into the ArrayList<Tasks>
in Grump.java.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add support for I/O redirection testing of Grump
commitResults.messageBody:
Add EXPECTED-UNIX.txt and input.txt for testing of Grump.
For future testing:
On mac: change EXPECTED-UNIX.txt and run runtest.sh
On windows: change EXPECTED.txt and run runtest.bat

commitResults.messageTitle: Add 2 custom exceptions and support for error handling in Grump.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Add InvalidCommandException.java and MissingArgException.java.
InvalidCommandException will be thrown if user fails to provide a valid
command such as list, bye, todo <arg>, etc.
MissingArgException will be thrown if user wants to add a task but does
not provide the correct number of arguments.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add support for delete in Grump.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Add support for delete. User can input the 'delete' command
followed by the task number. Error handling for missing or invalid
task number is also added.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Command.java and support for enums in Grump.java
commitResults.messageBody:
Add Command.java which is the enum for the commands allowed in Grump.
Add support for using the enum Command for the logic flow in Grump.java
